com.skyisland.questmanager.scheduling

Interface Tickable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BankNPC, CountdownRequirement, DummyNPC, ForgeNPC, InnNPC, LevelupNPC, MuteNPC, NPC, PlayerManager, QuestMonsterNPC, ServiceNPC, ShopNPC, SimpleBioptionNPC, SimpleChatNPC, SimpleNPC, SimpleQuestStartNPC, SimpleStaticBioptionNPC, Summon, TeleportNPC, TimeRequirement

    public interface Tickable
    An object is Tickable if they can be ticked. All tickable objects can register with a scheduler and then be visited by ticks.

    Some easy applications of ticks are movement patterns, regular regeneration, etc

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void tick()
      Performs a scheduled 'tick'.

    • Method Detail

      • tick

        void tick()
        Performs a scheduled 'tick'. This method can mean anything a Tickable class wants it to be. Scheduled Tickable classes receive calls to this on a scheduled and regular basis
